headlines.description: Matt Mobley scored 26 points and grabbed a key rebound with 4.2 seconds left, and St. Bonaventure beat Rhode Island 77-74 to snap the 16th-ranked Rams' 16-game winning streak on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: St. Bonaventure upsets No. 16 Rhode Island with 77-74 win

video.headline: St. Bonaventure upsets No. 16 Rhode Island

headlines.description: CJ Massinburg had 24 points, 12 rebounds and five assists and Buffalo clinched the Mid-American Conference East Division title on Friday night with a 95-82 win over Bowling Green.
headlines.shortLinkText: Buffalo clinches MAC East with 95-82 win over Bowling Green

headlines.description: James Towns scored 20 points, Kahlil Dukes added 17 and the pair fueled a second-half rally after Niagara lost high-scoring guard Matt Scott to edge Iona 85-84 on Friday night in a meeting of the third- and fourth-place teams in the Metro Atlantic...
headlines.shortLinkText: Niagara overcomes loss of Scott in 85-84 win over Iona

headlines.description: Isaiah Reese had 26 points and matched a career-high with six steals to lead Canisius to a 78-60 victory over Monmouth on Friday night for its sixth straight win.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reese scores 26 points, leads Canisius over Monmouth 79-60

headlines.description: Seth Towns had seven of his 24 points in the final 3 1/2 minutes, Christian Juzang added a career-high 21 points, and Harvard survived with a 65-58 win over Brown on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Harvard beats Brown 65-58, stays tied for first in Ivy

video.headline: Harvard moves to 8-1 in Ivy League play  - Via Ivy League

headlines.description: Devon Goodman, who had scored 35 points all season, came off the bench to hit five 3-pointers and piled up 23 points to lead Pennsylvania to a 74-62 victory on Friday night that kept the Quakers tied with Harvard atop the Ivy League.
headlines.shortLinkText: Goodman's big night helps give Penn 74-62 win over Columbia

video.headline: Penn rallies from early deficit to upend Columbia  - Via Ivy League

headlines.description: Blake Reynolds scored 17 points, Miye Oni added 15 and Yale rolled to a 77-65 victory over Dartmouth on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Reynolds, Oni lead Yale over Dartmouth 77-65

video.headline: Yale downs Dartmouth in Ivy League play  - Via Ivy League

headlines.description: Jalen Hayes scored 24 points and Oakland beat Cleveland State 82-66 on Friday night to give coach Greg Kampe his 600th career victory.
Kameron Chatman had his ninth double-double of the season with 26 points and 11 rebounds to help Detroit Mercy beat Youngstown State 94-84 on Friday night.
Matt Morgan scored nine of his 31 points in triple-overtime and Cornell snapped a six-game losing skid against Princeton with a 107-101 victory on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Morgan scores 31, Cornell beats Princeton 107-101 in 3OT

video.headline: Cornell caps historic comeback in 3 OT win over Princeton  - Via Ivy League

headlines.description: T.J. Henderson's baseline 3-pointer gave IUPUI the lead with 50 seconds left in overtime and Jaylen Minnett then scored his only three points from the line to wrap up the Jaguars' 76-71 victory over Milwaukee on Friday night.
Tookie Brown scored 23 points and Georgia Southern knocked off rival Georgia State 85-80 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brown scores 23, leads Georgia Southern over Georgia State

headlines.description: Dikembe Dixson scored 18 points, Jordan Blount had 14 points and 15 rebounds and Illinois-Chicago beat Green Bay 83-75 on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Dixson scores 18, leads UIC over Green Bay 83-75

headlines.description: Loudon Love scored 15 points and Wright State held off a late rally from Northern Kentucky 69-67 in a matchup of the Horizon League's top two teams on Friday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Wright State beats Northern Kentucky in Horizon showdown

nowFeed.headline: Oklahoma's Trae Young, on his recent offensive struggles: "Im getting guarded like nobody else in the country is being guarded, scouted on like no one else in the country. Its a mystery coming out each and every game to try and figure out how a team is going to guard me and how Im going to dictate how my team wins.  Its a lot tougher for me to score now than it was in the beginning. ... Its a process. Right now, its tough."
